SIMPLE: production
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Production
<hw>Pro*duc"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>productio</ets> a lengthening, prolonging: cf. F.
<ets>production</ets>. See <er>Produce</er>. ]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The act or process or producing, bringing forth, or
exhibiting to view; <as>as, the <ex>production</ex> of commodities, of a
witness</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which is produced, yielded, or made, whether
naturally, or by the application of intelligence and labor; <as>as, the
<ex>productions</ex> of the earth; the <ex>productions</ex> of
handicraft; the <ex>productions</ex> of intellect or
genius.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The act of lengthening out or prolonging.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Product; produce; fruit; work; performance;
composition.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Productive</ent>⟦br⟧
